wikipedia_page.main: William Booth (9 May 1886 – 1963) was an English professional football centre half who played in the Football League for Sheffield United. He made 369 appearances for Brighton & Hove Albion and was a member of the team that won the 1909–10 Southern League First Division title and the 1910 FA Charity Shield. Booth was a non-playing reserve for England in February 1913.
